'''Wiley''' was a male [[Wokling/Legends|wokling]] who lived on the [[Endor/Legends|forest moon of Endor]]. He was the son of [[Lumat/Legends|Lumat]] and [[Zephee/Legends|Zephee]] and the brother of [[Latara/Legends|Latara]] and [[Nippet/Legends|Nippet]].<ref name="Baby Ewoks" /> Wiley was named after a [[Wiley (legend)|legendary hunter]] in Ewok mythology.<ref name="GCG">''[[Galactic Campaign Guide]]''</ref>

{{Char-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
Wiley was one of six 8-inch plush woklings made by [[Kenner Products|Kenner]] based upon the six woklings seen in [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Return of the Jedi'']]. While the character names of [[Malani]], [[Nippet/Legends|Nippet]], and Wiley were established prior in the [[Ewoks (television series)|''Ewoks'']] television series, the other three&mdash;[[Mookiee]], [[Leeni]], and [[Gwig]]&mdash;have yet to be attributed to their respective characters seen in ''Return of the Jedi''.

